<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Tell-tale" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Tell-tale,</orth> one who gives mischievous information about the concerns of other persons: <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.2.133" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 2, 133</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.4.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 4, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 5.123" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. V, 123</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.1.202" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 1, 202</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.3.117" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 3, 117</bibl>. Adjectively: <cit><quote>the t. day,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 806" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 806</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>these t. women,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.149" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 149</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>